<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-380-456  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 380 456.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  April 23 1990 v11 n17 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Railroad manages training with automated scheduler.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Feuche, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Structured Query Language (SQL) database query is providingthe railroad industry with an automated employee tracking systemthat allows them to monitor the training and retraining of enginedrivers, switchmen, dispatchers and other field employee.andO;Employee training is critical to safety practice and compliance torules set by the Federal Railroad Administration (FRA).andP;  Employeeinformation is stored in an employee file that includes worker'sname, social security number, job classification and associatedrules, promotion dates, test scores, dates of courses previouslyattended and dates of scheduled courses.andP;  Efficient test datamanagement is important in case of an accident where the FRA mustbe informed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Railroad IndustryEmployee RelationsInformation Resources ManagementTraining of EmployeesUnited States. Federal Railroad Administration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>